18: As in... They do everything for you?!
23:
That's right. They come equipped
with a dryer too! The conveniences
of the modern world are incredible,
aren't they!
42:
Alk, dear, are you okay?! Blink twice if
you need medical attention!
47:
I'm fine... But this is AMAZING! Wow,
technological progress is incredible!
We really do have a bright future
ahead of us!
52:
We asked Regis to manufacture
these for us. He based them off
blueprints we found in the Endless
Blue.
56:
Regis did something useful for once!
This might be the first time I've ever
been glad to hear his name.
60:
We also installed dishwashers in the
kitchen.
72:
Well... Today I learned that when you
get TOO happy, you can start to
have trouble breathing.
80:
I'm not familiar with this tool—does it
really make such a significant
difference?
86:
Yes! It does! I'll save SO much time
doing laundry now I won't know
what to do with it all!
96:
I see. If this development has
afforded you some time, why not
use it for yourself? We're in the
middle of a festival, after all. Have
fun.
102:
Yeah! I was just thinking about
coming up with some new dishes
and increasing my repertoire.
106: Or maybe not? I-is that bad?
111:
I mean, if it's what you wanna do, I
won't be stopping you.
115:
If cooking truly is so important to
you, why not make a trade of it? You
could sell your dishes and make
some profit.
118:
Of course I don't mean to suggest
you should do that right away, but
maybe after we complete our
present mission. What do you think?
127:
I suppose I do consider myself to be
somewhat good at cooking... But I
don't think I'm good enough to try to
make it as a pro chef.
130:
I'm satisfied with where my skills are
right now.
135:
Hmm. If that is truly how you feel,
then so be it.
138:
Well then. It's been a while since
we've had the pleasure of eating
your cooking. Would you care to
indulge us tonight?
149:
Happy 50th Kaleidoscope
anniversary, everyone! We're not
gonna let a little thing like
rampaging dragons interrupt OUR
festivities, are we? Haha!
153:
Coming up next, the culinary
festival! Starting with a... FOOD
FIGHT! The cooking kind, not the
food-throwing one.
158:
Um?
What is going on? Why am I here?
161:
Y-you told me I was WATCHING the
event! Why am I in the middle of the
arena?!
165:
To participate in the contest, of
course! Come on, Alk, time to give it
your all!
173:
I asked a certain explosion-loving
ninja to help me out. She disguised
herself as you and signed up on
your behalf!
181:
Alk, dearie. I know that you don't
want to make your cooking into a
competition.
183:
And it's true that you don't need to
dedicate your life to refining and
mastering your craft. You're not
wrong.
186:
However, I draw the line at you
calling yourself "not good enough"!
That I cannot tolerate!
192:
It is true that perhaps your
knowledge and skills are not
sufficiently developed. But you have
the perfect SENSE for cooking!
196:
You've felt the overwhelming
happiness and pride that comes
when you brighten another person's
day with your dishes!
198:
Don't forget that it I too placed my
confidence in you and chose you as
my pupil! To devalue your own skills
is to question my judgment!
201: I wasn't trying to do that, I'm sorry!
203:
Me being too hard on myself made
you feel bad, huh...
208:
Well, maybe just a bit. I suppose that
comes purely from my own
selfishness.
210:
Well then, Alk. Would you be a dear
and join your master in this cooking
contest?
214:
When you put it that way, I guess I
have no choice!
217: Let's do our best to win this thing!
223:
Second place? So frustratingly
close! Just a bit more and he would
have won the entire event.
227:
And after I gave that whole
grandiose speech to convince him
too... I feel terrible for the poor boy.
232: It's not a problem. He will be okay.
237:
If you're worried about the kid, why
not sneak past his room later? See
how he's doing.
245:
Holy CRAP! I can't believe I got
second place!
